<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="484" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1122,1471]" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from other genera in Pyriglenini by scalloped underparts of males (solid black in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,269,1339,1363]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmeciza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), black ear covert patches, extensively rufous brown plumage, and broadly tipped blackish wing coverts. Open cup nests on ground, loudsongs consisting of doublets, and flicking tail movements distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[151,294,1410,1435]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,294,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">Myrmoderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other clades in Pyriglenini except 
<taxonomicName box="[759,888,1410,1435]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Hylophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[759,888,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">Hylophylax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. Proportionately long tail and slender bill identified by Ridgway as generic characters apply only to 
<taxonomicName box="[803,903,1446,1471]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis box="[803,903,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">loricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1080,1447,1470]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamosus">
<emphasis box="[957,1080,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">squamosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
